            <abstract>
                <p>The α-recension of the Tārika Walda ʾAmid is the first translation of this work from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz. According to a
                    colophon in the text, the translation took place at the time of <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY"/>. It contains only the 
                    pre-Islamic part, but not the parts on the history after the rise of Islam and no list of patriarchs as the 
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6936TarWaAmidBeta">β-recension</ref>. According to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Diez2024Amid"/>
                    <citedRange unit="page">140-141</citedRange></bibl> both recension have been translated from the 'old recension' of the 
                    Arabic version of the Tārīḫ Ibn al-ʿAmīd, that is represented by the manuscript ANT of the Antonius monastery in Egypt.</p>
            </abstract>
